6 An Act relating to assault and battery; amending 21
O.S. 2021, Section 650, which relates to aggravated
7 assault and battery upon a peace officer; modifying
scope of certain unlawful act; defining term;
8 updating statutory language; and providing an
effective date.
9
10
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 21 O.S. 2021, Section 650, is
13 amended to read as follows:
14 Section 650. A. Every person who, without justifiable or
15 excusable cause, knowingly commits any aggravated assault and
16 battery upon the person of a police officer, sheriff, deputy sheriff
17 or, highway patrolman, corrections personnel as defined in Section
18 649 of this title, or any state peace officer employed by any state
19 or federal governmental agency to enforce state laws, while the
20 officer is in the performance of his or her duties shall, upon
21 conviction thereof, be guilty of a felony, which shall be punishable
22 by imprisonment in the custody of the Department of Corrections for
23 not more than life or by, a fine not exceeding One Thousand Dollars
24 ($1,000.00), or by both such fine and imprisonment.
ENGR. S. B. NO. 369 Page 1
1 B. Every person who, without justifiable or excusable cause,
2 commits any aggravated assault and battery upon a person that the
3 violator knows or should reasonably know is a police officer,
4 sheriff, deputy sheriff or, highway patrolman, corrections personnel
5 as defined in Section 649 of this title, or any state peace officer
6 employed by any state or federal governmental agency to enforce
7 state laws, that results in maiming as defined in Section 751 of
8 this title, while the officer is in the performance of his or her
9 duties shall, upon conviction, be guilty of a felony punishable by
10 imprisonment in the custody of the Department of Corrections of for
11 not less than five (5) years nor more than life or by, a fine not
12 exceeding Five Thousand Dollars ($5,000.00), or by both such fine
13 and imprisonment.
14 C. For purposes of this section, aggravated assault and battery
15 upon law officers, includes the:
16 1. The physical contact with and in an attempt to gain control
17 of the firearm; or
18 2. The strangulation,
19 of any police officer, sheriff, deputy sheriff, highway patrolman,
20 corrections personnel as defined in Section 649 of this title, or
21 any peace officer employed by any state or federal governmental
22 agency to enforce state laws.
23 As used in this subsection, “strangulation” shall have the same
24 meaning as provided in subsection J of Section 644 of this title.
ENGR. S. B. NO. 369 Page 2
1 D. This section shall not supersede any other act or acts, but
2 shall be cumulative thereto.
3 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
4 Passed the Senate the 25th day of March, 2025.
